Table 1: Experimental results on 6 benchmarking datasets from Dwivedi et al. [15]. Results on PATTERN and CLUSTER 
datasets are given in terms of weighted accuracy. Red: best model, Violet: good model; arrow next to a metric indicates whether 
higher or lower is better. Results not shown are not available for that method.

Table 2: Results on OGB-LSC PCQM4M and PCQM4Mv2 
datasets in terms of Mean Absolute Error (lower is better). 
Results not shown are not available.

Table 3: Results on OGB Mol datasets. EGT uses trans-
fer learning from PCQM4Mv2, whereas GIN-VN and 
Graphormer use transfer learning from PCQM4M. AP 
stands for Average Precision and AUC for Area Under the 
ROC Curve, higher is better for both. Results not shown are 
not available.
